<F P=100> Yugoslavia </F>
<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Chairman on Scope of Albanian Issues </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0601140194 Tirana ATA in English 1305 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0601140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 6 (ATA) -- "The issue of Kosovar 
Albanians is a great political problem. All are aware of the 
bad situation of human rights in Kosova. I know that the issue 
of Albanians is more profound and it is not limited only to 
human rights," Vesna Peshic, chairman of Civil Alliance Party in 
Belgrade said in an interview with the independent newspaper 
DITA INFORMACION. 
  Vesnia Peshic, professor of philosophy and sociology at the 
Belgrade University, is considered by Milovan Gjilasi, the most 
renowned Yugoslav dissident, as the only representative of the 
opposition that should be appreciated. Mrs. Peshic wrote in the 
book A Goridan Knot, should it be cut or...? that thus far it 
has been spoken of Albanians raping the Serbs but statistics 
show of the opposite. Because of this attitude Mrs. Pashic was 
declared traitor by the Belgrade government. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

