<F P=100> Yugoslavia </F>
<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Albanian Men Forced To Join Serbian Army </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0901151194 Tirana ATA in English 0910 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0901151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 9 (ATA) -- Fifty Albanian young 
fellows from Kosova were forcefully recruited by the Serbian 
Army during 1993. This is a special form of the repression of 
Serbian officials, a report of the Human Rights and Freedoms 
Defence Council in Prishtina said. The data provided by the 
report show that Albanian fellows who were forced to join the 
Serbian Army were born from 1966 to 1974. Most of them were 
arrested in streets or their homes and some of them were brought 
to military court. All Albanian recruits were sent to the 
barracks of the Serbian Army established outside Kosova. 

</TEXT>

