<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commission Details Serb Border Shootings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0701173694 Tirana ATA in English 0910 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0701173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 6 (ATA) -- The spokesman of the 
Ministry of Public Order informed ATA on January 5 that in the 
region of D-14/18 border sign, only 5.5 metres in the Yugoslav 
territory, at about 1030 [0930 GMT], the Albanian citizen 
Ramadan Ibrahim Mustafa, 25 years, from the village Kosharisht 
of Kukes was killed. 
  Regarding this incident, the local mixed commission for 
resolution of border incidents gathered immediately. From 
verification in the spot it came out that the victim had passed 
the border while scything, immediately he was hit by Serbian 
patrol at a very small distance of 15 metres. 
  The commission also found in the spot nine shells of a 
machine gun of the type 1-K, 1976. The victim has been hit from 
behind with five bullets starting with the hips up to the 
shoulders. The victim has been carried along for 6-7 meters, 
parallel with the border line. His coat and cardigan were put 
off his body. 
  The spokesman reports of another border incident on January 
2, in the vicinity of the border, 30 meters in the Albanian 
territory, in the border sign D/6 in the zone of Tropoje, at 
about 1530. Regarding this second incident, the spokesman 
reports that the Serbian border patrol shot on the Albanian 
national Hamit Ram Sallaku, 20 years, while he was with his 
sheep. The wounded has been sent immediately in the Tropoje 
hospital where he is being treated. 
  Since the beginning of 1993, the number of Albanian victims 
in the Yugoslav-Albanian border amounts to 21. 

</TEXT>

