<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Tudjman-Izetbegovic Talks in Bonn </TI></H3>
<H4>   Croatian Map Includes Vitez, Busovaca </H4>
<F P=102> LD1001195394 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1830 
GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001195394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] During our news bulletin we received the details of 
the latest Croatian map proposal defining the demarcation 
between the Muslim and the Croat community in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. Under this proposal, the Croat republic of 
Herceg-Bosna would include, among other areas, Vitez, Busovaca, 
and Bugojno. 

</TEXT>

