<H3> <TI>   Kovac, Meciar To Lead Prague Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001202994 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Slovak delegation at the Prague meeting of 
representatives of Visegrad Group countries with U.S. President 
Bill Clinton will be composed of President Michal Kovac, Prime 
Minister Vladimir Meciar, and Minister of Foreign Affairs Jozef 
Moravcik. It will probably also include deputy prime ministers 
Jozef Prokes, Sergej Kozlik, and Julius Toth, and Minister of 
the Economy Jan Ducky. Our delegation will leave for Prague 
tomorrow afternoon. 
  Michal Kovac will also hold talks on Wednesday with Czech 
President Vaclav Havel and Hungarian President Arpad Goncz. He 
will also meet his Polish counterpart, Lech Walesa. 
  Bilateral talks of prime ministers and ministers of foreign 
affairs of the Slovak Republic and the Czech Republic and, 
naturally, bilateral talks of our representatives with the U.S. 
delegation are also expected. 

</TEXT>

