<H3> <TI>   Kovac Favors Cooperation of Visegrad Countries </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001214994 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001214994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Michal Kovac is prepared to receive 
information about the Brussels NATO meeting, which is to be 
given by President Clinton to the top officials of the Visegrad 
Four states during their meeting in Prague. 
  Answering a question from TASR [Slovak news agency] 
concerning his opinion on the cooperation of Visegrad Four 
countries in their effort to join NATO, Michal Kovac said he 
personally believes coordination and cooperation will help the 
countries involved get incorporated into this security 
structure, although Partnership for Peace is a project to be 
concluded with the alliance by each individual country 
separately. 

