<H3> <TI>   Kovac Discusses Minority Policy With Hungarians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701204194 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0701204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Bratislava this afternoon, Slovak President 
Michal Kovac received for the first time personally 
representatives of the Hungarian Civic Party [HCP]. Anton Bodis, 
the president's spokesman, will now tell us about the 
preliminary results of that meeting. He is at this moment on the 
other end of the telephone line. Good evening. Can one already 
talk about some specific conclusions from that meeting? 
  [Bodis] Good evening. HCP Chairman Laszlo Nagy briefed the 
president about the proposals, which his party sees as being 
possible ways of improving the position of national minorities 
in Slovakia. 
  The final conclusions will be known as soon as the president 
has studied these proposals in greater detail. The HCP chairman 
also briefed the president about the party's attitude to 
tomorrow's meeting in Komarno. The president voiced the hope 
that the meeting will take place in a calm and 
nonconfrontational tone. 
  Michal Kovac appreciated the realistic and tolerant attitude 
adopted by the HCP to relations between Slovaks and the 
Hungarian national minority, and toward ways of improving them. 
Both sides agreed on the need to outline the national policy of 
the Slovak Republic and ways of implementing it. 

</TEXT>

