<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council Urges Hungarians To Reassess Actions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701232494 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0701232494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Bratislava City Council today discussed the 
appeal issued by the Association of Towns and Villages of Zitny 
Ostrov, as well as the question of to what extent it concerns 
self-administration of the capital city of the Slovak Republic. 
In the statement given today to the Press Agency of the Slovak 
Republic, Bratislava Mayor Peter Kresanek believes, along with 
members of the City Council, that sound reason, responsibility, 
and the interests of all citizens of the Slovak Republic will 
prevail. 
  The City Council appeals to mayors of the Association of 
Towns and Villages of Zitny ostrov with a feeling of regret and 
misgiving that, instead of taking a common approach in pushing 
through self-administrative structures and interests of the 
citizens-voters, they have chosen a path of unrealistic demands 
that do not represent a real interest of the inhabitants of the 
towns and villages of that region. 
  In the statement, Mayor Kresanek and members of the 
Bratislava City Council, addressing their colleagues from the 
Association of Towns and Villages of Zitny ostrov, call for 
well-considered conduct and a fundamental reassessment of the 
course they have taken up to now, which otherwise might lead to 
raising nationalistic passions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-49413 </DOCNO>
