<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gazprom Company To Supply More Russian Gas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001220094 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001220094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister Sergej Kozlik received Rem 
Ivanovich Vyasirev, president of the Russian company Gazprom, in 
Bratislava today. Mr. Vyasirev briefed the deputy prime minister 
on the deliveries of Russian gas for Slovakia. The two officials 
agreed to increase shipments of natural gas to Slovakia to 5.5 
billion cubic meters this year. They have also assessed the 
possibilities of a long-term contract for the year 2005, which 
should represent the delivery of 10-11 billion cubic meters of 
natural gas for Slovakia. 

</TEXT>

