<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reaction to Brussels Summit Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Zhelev Comments on Membership </H4>
<F P=102> AU0701155294 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1400 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0701155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The traditional New Year reception given by 
President Dr. Zhelev for the diplomatic corps took place at the 
Boyana Residence today. 
  In greeting the diplomats, Dr. Zhelev expressed his 
confidence that, as in the past, also in 1994, their benevolence 
and good intentions toward Bulgaria are likely to contribute to 
our country's efforts for international support. Bulgarian 
democracy has reached the middle of its first seven years and is 
still expected to accomplish a great deal, but the path of 
changes that Bulgaria embarked upon four years ago is 
irreversible, the president assured his audience. 
  Mr. Zhelev recalled the essence of Bulgaria's international 
policy and its Balkan policy in particular, which is aimed at 
building lasting good neighborly and mutually advantageous 
relations. 
  Dwelling on the forthcoming summit meeting of the NATO 
member-states scheduled for 10 January 1994, the Bulgarian head 
of state pointed out our country's stand of principle, according 
to which it is striving to join NATO after the North Atlantic 
bloc has, possibly, decided to expand. 

</TEXT>

