<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Passes Temporary Budget for Jan-Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001173794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1614 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001173794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 10 Jan (TANJUG) -- The federal government 
met today and discussed and passed a decree on providing 
temporary financing for the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia for 
the period of January-March 1994, the federal Ministry of 
Information reports in a statement. The session was chaired by 
Deputy Prime Minister Zeljko Simic. 
  As the conditions have not been fulfilled for this year's 
federal budget to be adopted by the Federal Assembly by the end 
of the year, and in order not to threaten the most vital 
functions of the federal state, the Federal Republic of 
Yugoslavia Government passed an act on a temporary budget for 
the first quarter of the year. 
  This will make it possible to secure resources to finance 
the 
work of the Army of Yugoslavia and the fedaral administration 
bodies, pay war veteran's pensions and social security, provide 
social security for refugees and for the population on the 
territories under the control of the UN peacekeeping forces, the 
statement says. 

</TEXT>

