<H3> <TI>   Kontic Receives New Head of Observer Mission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001153694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1306 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001153694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 10 Jan (TANJUG) -- [Yugoslav] Federal 
Prime Minister Dr. Radoje Kontic received Konstantin 
Gorokostapulos [name as received], head of the EU observer 
mission for the former Yugoslavia, who took over this post on 1 
January. During the meeting it was stressed that it is vital to 
do everything to end the conflicts in the former 
Bosnia-Herzegovina peacefully as soon as possible. It was 
pointed out that the EU mission could play a significant role in 
this connection, above all by interpreting events in the area of 
the former Yugoslavia objectively. To this end the Federal 
Government and federal bodies will offer all necessary 
assistance to the EU mission. 
  Interest was expressed on both sides in the closest possible 
cooperation between the Federal Government and federal organs 
and the EU mission, the statement of the Federal Information 
Ministry says in conclusion. 

