<H3> <TI>   Albanian Killed by Army Guards at Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001161694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1520 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001161694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 10 Jan (TANJUG) -- The information service 
of the Yugoslav Army's Third Army [as received] has said in a 
statement that at 1350 today a new border incident took place 
near the Morina border watch-tower on the border with Albania. 
The incident was caused by the Albanian side. Yugoslav Army 
border guards killed an Albanian citizen, who had tried 
illegally to cross the border and had refused to obey their 
orders, on FRY territory. Competent investigating officers have 
been sent to the scene of the killing in order to establish all 
the circumstances relating to the killing of the person who 
tried illegally to cross the border, the statement concludes. 

</TEXT>

