<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cluster Bombs, Chemicals Used in Vitez Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101115194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1000 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101115194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] After a relatively quiet night, the Muslim army 
began fresh artillery and infantry actions this morning. Ivica 
Saric reports for Croatian radio. 
  [Saric] In addition to the shelling of Vitez, the positions 
of the Croat Defense Council [HVO] in the Buhine Kuce region 
came under fire at 0900. Heavy machine guns are being used in 
the main. The enemy began infantry attacks in the direction of 
the Vitez operational zone at 0930 with the intention of 
restoring control over the buildings it lost yesterday in Buhine 
Kuce. Fierce street fighting and a battle for every house has 
resumed. The defense formations are successfully repelling the 
attacks by the Muslim army. 
  In the Vitez operational zone, they have evidence that in 
yesterday's shelling of Vitez the Muslim army used a type of 
cluster bomb. This refers to mortars which prior to exploding 
release dozens of the notorious bomblets which explode on 
impact. In addition to this, a number of shells which fell on 
Mali Mosunj in the municipality of Vitez were filled with 
chemicals. People felt sick and dizzy and there were visible 
traces of an inky color in those houses which were hit. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

