<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Estimated Revenues From Privatization Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001225194 Prague Stanica Praha Radio Network in Czech 
2130 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001225194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Stanica Praha Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] A news conference about privatization took place 
in Prague today. Jitka Kucerova has more details. 
  [Kucerova] According to Roman Ceska, first deputy minister 
for the administration and privatization of the national 
property, 90 percent of the property earmarked for privatization 
has already undergone the approval procedure at the ministry and 
has been handed over to the National Property Fund. Revenues 
from both small- and large-scale privatization are estimated at 
54 billion korunas [Kc] so far. Mr. Ceska also said the small 
scale privatization was completed at the end of 1993. Any 
property remaining will be privatized by large-scale 
privatization methods. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

