<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Unemployment Totaled 3.34 Percent in Nov </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101094494 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 0600 
GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the end of November 1993, the Czech Republic 
state budget showed a surplus of 2.7 billion Czech korunas. This 
transpires from the data of the Czech Statistical Office 
released yesterday [10 January]. The number of unemployed has 
increased to 175,800, while the number of job vacancies has 
dropped to approximately 55,000. Thus, the number of unemployed 
was three times higher in November than the number of job 
vacancies. Two-thirds of the unemployed are workers. The 
unemployment rate was 3.34 percent. 

</TEXT>

