<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   MDF Not To Form Coalition With MSZP </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1001144394 Budapest MTI in English 2037 GMT 7 Jan 93 </F>
<F P=103> AU1001144394 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 7 January (MTI) -- The Hungarian 
Democratic Forum (MDF) continues to exclude the possibility of 
forming coalitions with any successor parties of the former 
Hungarian Socialist Workers' Party, MDF Vice-President and 
Parliamentary Group Head Ferenc Kulin told reporters in Budapest 
on Friday [7 January]. 
  During the 1994 electoral campaign, Hungary's main coalition 
party will do its utmost to prevent the Hungarian Socialist 
Party (MSZP) from having the chance to form a government, he 
said. 
  The MDF does not want to enter into coalition with parties 
which disagree with its nationally-committed policy and do not 
recognize the values of a conservative center-right policy, 
Kulin asserted. 
  Asked by MTI, the politician thought it impossible for the 
MDF to make a coalition with the Alliance of Free Democrats. 
Any further guesses were meaningless -- the MDF would not look 
at alliances with other parties before knowing election results. 

</TEXT>

