<H3> <TI>   Further on Ethnic Hungarians Meeting in Komarno </TI></H3>
<H4>   SNS Rejects Legitimacy of Meeting </H4>
<F P=102> AU1001201294 Prague CTK in English 2015 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1001201294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, Jan 9 (CTK) -- Local representatives 
and mayors of villages have no authority to hold the kind of 
meeting that took place in Komarno, southern Slovakia, on 
Saturday [8 January], Slovak National Party (SNS) deputy 
Vladimir Miskovsky told Slovak Television this evening. 
  Answers to the call on Slovak constitutional officials by 
the 
meeting of ethnic Hungarian representatives would legitimize the 
demands expressed at the meeting, he said. 
  Miskovsky also said that the issues of two official 
languages 
and ethnic autonomy for the Hungarian minority in Slovakia were 
unacceptable for the SNS. 

