<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Yugoslavia: Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council Reports on Albanian Human Rights Cases </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0801170494 Tirana ATA in English 1120 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0801170494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pristina, January 8 (ATA) -- The Council for the 
Protection of Human Rights and Freedoms in Prishtina has 
reported that during 1993 there were 13,431 cases of police 
violence against the Albanian population in Kosova. As a result 
of this abusive police action, fifteen Albanians were killed and 
fourteen wounded. Last year, 2,305 people were arrested, 62 
punished for minor infringements, and 49 sentenced for felonies. 
The police carried out raids on 1,994 families, and 849 persons 
were subjected to interrogation by the Serbian police. 1,777 
persons were maltreated physically, and 794 people suffered 
other sorts of abuse from the Serbian authorities. During this 
period, there were 391 cases of property being forcibly taken by 
the Serbian forces. There were 172 cases of using violence 
against children. 
  During last year in Kosova, 68 people were forced from their 
jobs, and 53 Albanian families were evicted from their homes. 
Finally, there were 155 cases of violence against women. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

