<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coalition Chairman on Successes of Past Year </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0701064694 Prague CTK in English 1553 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0701064694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague Jan 6 (CTK) -- The Czech Republic's 
undisputable economic success and social peace, which testify to 
the government's flexible social policy, were the major 
positives of the last year, Josef Lux, agriculture minister and 
chairman of the government coalition Christian Democratic 
Union-Czechoslovak People's Party (KDU-CSL), said today. 
  The current social tranquility in the Czech Republic 
testifies also to the people's willingness to accept the road 
that had been embarked on, along with the problems which 
accompany it, Lux told journalists. He added that it was of key 
importance that social peace be preserved this year as well. 
Lux said that while implementing the principles of a market 
economy, the government had actually managed to establish the 
principle of a social market economy -- social consideration. 
  He said he firmly believed that in the process of the 
general 
denationalisation of state-owned enterprises, trade unions 
should play an active role as a mediator between employers and 
employees and that the KDU-CSL intended to support them. 
  As regards the envisaged five-percent unemployment, the 
KDU-CSL considered it necessary and acceptable, said Lux, adding 
that he considered the number of employed to be less important 
than the period of time during which people have no jobs. He 
pointed to the necessity of a more active implementation of 
regional policy in problematic regions and especially in areas 
with high unemployment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

