<H3> <TI>   Patriarch Denies Endorsing Macedonian Church </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101193294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1435 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Belgrade, 11 Jan (TANJUG) -- Serbian Patriarch 
Pavle has never said that the Macedonians have the right to 
their own church at any of the meetings between delegations of 
the Serbian Orthodox Church and representatives of the 
self-proclaimed Macedonian Orthodox Church, Patriarch Pavle's 
office said in a statement today. This was the reaction of the 
Belgrade Patriarchate to the claim by Archbishop Mihail, 
newly-elected head of the Macedonian Orthodox Church, which have 
recently been published in the media, that Patriarch Pavle said 
that "Macedonians are a people, they have their state, and they 
have the right to have their own church." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

