<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Rail Links Envisaged With Bulgaria </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1201080494 Skopje MIC in English 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1201080494 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Railroad Track Macedonia-Bulgaria"] </F>
  [Text] The railroad link up of Macedonia with Bulgaria is 
soon expected to be realized. In Macedonia, two lines, in the 
direction Kocani-Blagoevgrad (Bulgaria) or Kumanovo-Guesevo 
(Bulgaria), are envisaged. The route Kocani-Blagoevgrad 
foresees the construction of a new track long 145 km, and which 
will cost $430 million. The second route Kumanovo-Guesevo 
consists of a track long 46 km, at the cost of $120 million. 
The direction Kumanovo-Guesevo is given the advantage, in view 
of the costs and the quick realization. The public in Kocani is 
complaining about this and believes that the government is not 
well informed as to the advantages of this route, which would 
connect their own town with Bulgaria. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

