<H3> <TI>   Ministry Concerned Over Hungarian Activity </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101225294 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101225294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ivo Hlavacek, the director of the legal and consular 
department in the Slovak Foreign Affairs Ministry, handed over 
to Jenoe Boros, the Hungarian charge d'affaires, in Bratislava 
today a written statement in which the ministry expresses its 
concern over the activity of the Hungarian governmental office 
for Hungarian minorities abroad. The specific reason for the 
ministry's concern is that this office drafted and disseminated 
in foreign diplomatic circles information on the so-called 
Komarno initiative that takes matters out of context and, 
according to our ministry, is nonobjective and misleading. The 
Foreign Ministry said Slovakia did all it could to meet specific 
obligations it had accepted on joining the Council of Europe. 

</TEXT>

