<H3> <TI>   Border Guard Seeks Armored Vehicles From China </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001155894 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1400 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001155894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The border guard wishes to obtain at least 100 
armored carriers from China in exchange for China's state debts. 
The vehicles would be given to the 19 border patrol companies. 
The Nikex joint stock company, which has been commissioned by 
the Ministry of the Interior to conclude the deal, announced 
that a Hungarian delegation is to travel to Beijing in the next 
few days in order to gather information. China owes Hungary 
over seven billion forints. 

</TEXT>

