<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnia May Boycott Western Goods </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201121694 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 1130 GMT 
12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Muslim-led Bosnian Government intends to ask 
friendly countries to boycott Western products if NATO does not 
decide to intervene militarily in Bosnia in the near future. The 
Bosnian ambassador to the United Nations, Muhamed Secirbegovic, 
announcing the planned boycott request on Dutch television, said 
it would go out mainly to Muslim countries. Mr. Secirbegovic 
said that the Bosnian Muslims feel betrayed by Western countries 
that make pledges but fail to translate them into action. The 
Bosnian ambassador said the international boycott must be 
directed against countries that obstruct military intervention. 

</TEXT>

