<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb Deputies Opt for No Change in Platform </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1101155294 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1101155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The session of the People's Assembly of the Srpska 
republic ended last night with a discussion behind closed doors 
on the peace negotiations in Geneva and Brussels. The deputies 
did not study possible corrections to the present platform as 
the political basis of the Serbian negotiating team. It was 
decided not to change anything in the essence of the political 
stands presently contained in the platform. The final decision 
regarding the platform will be made at the next assembly session 
in Bijeljina on 17 January, one day before the talks in Geneva. 

</TEXT>

