<H3> <TI>   Muslims Continue Attack on Vitez, Novi Travnik </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101190994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1816 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Zdenko Vranjes] </F>
  [Excerpt] The Muslim army today continued to attack the 
Vitez and Novi Travnik areas and a general alert was also 
sounded in Kiseljak. Heavy street fighting is still under way in 
the area of Buhine Kuce, on the eastern approaches to Vitez. The 
Muslim units, reinforced with new forces from Zenica, are still 
trying to regain the positions they lost yesterday and get 
access to the Vitez-Busovaca road. 
  The Muslim army continues to pound the center of Vitez, 
using 
mortars and heavy guns. Novi Travnik has also been shelled 
throughout the day, as have the surrounding areas held by the 
Croatian Defense Council [HVO]heavily pounded from the Muslim 
howitzers and mortars are the town centernd the area of 
Rastovci. It has been reported from Novi Travnik that the HVO 
repelled a heavy infantry attack on Relej, a hill near the town. 
The Muslim forces suffered a major defeat and were forced to 
withdraw, with heavy losses. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

