<H3> <TI>   Inter-Muslim Fighting Resumes in Cazin Krajina </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101132394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1224 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bihac, 11 Jan (TANJUG) -- Fierce inter-Muslim 
clashes resumed today in the Cazin Krajina along the entire 
demarcation line, local Muslim media reports. 
  According to the same sources, Fikret Abdic's forces have 
captured the villages of Trzac and Trzacke Rastele and members 
of the 5th Corps of the Bosnia-Herzegovina army have captured 
the village of Skokovi and a part of Pecigrad. 
  According to the Western Bosnian News Agency and Radio 
Velkaton, both based in Velika Kladusa, sporadic clashes are 
taking place near Cumluk and Todorovo and new movements of 
troops loyal to Alija Izetbegovic have been registered near 
Buzim and Podic. [passage omitted] 

