<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dumitru Popa Appointed Head of TV Company </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1101183994 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1500 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1101183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A communique received from Romania's Government 
informs that, at an extraordinary session held today, Romania's 
Government approved -- following a report presented by Prime 
Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu -- the resignation request submitted 
by Mr. Paul Everac, director general of the Romanian Television, 
who had been appointed to that position by Governmental Decision 
No. 21/27 January 1993. In this respect, a new governmental 
decision was adopted, Governmental Decision No. 18, according to 
which Mr. Paul Everac is released from his position as of today. 
Until a law on the functioning of public radio and television 
services is passed, Mr. Dumitru Popa has been appointed to the 
position of general director of the Romanian Television. By 
another governmental decision, Mr. Dumitru Popa was released 
from his position as secretary of state, head of the 
Government's Public Information Department. 

</TEXT>

