<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on `Partnership for Peace' Meetings </TI></H3>
<H4>   Boross, Klaus on Visegrad Ties </H4>
<F P=102> LD1201173594 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1600 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hungarian Prime Minister Peter Boross has agreed 
with the Czech prime minister that there is no need for the 
Visegrad countries to formally institutionalize their ties. The 
Hungarian prime minister told this to journalists following 
talks with Czech Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus in Prague. 
According to Boross, Hungary is exposed to more dangers than 
the Czech Republic because of its geographical situation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

