<F P=102>  AU1201175994 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1201175994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today President Zhelyu Zhelev held a working meeting 
that was attended by Prime Minister Lyuben Berov, Foreign 
Minister Stanislav Daskalov, Defense Minister Valentin 
Aleksandrov, and Interior Minister Viktor Mikhaylov; General 
Lyuben Petrov, chief of the Bulgarian Army General Staff; 
Nikolay Slatinski, chairman of the Parliamentary National 
Security Commission; and Yunal Lyutfi, interim chairman of the 
Parliamentary Foreign Policy Commission. 
  Here is what the president's spokesman Valentin Stoyanov had 
to say about the results of the meeting: 
  [Begin Stoyanov recording] The participants in the 
conference 
discussed the theses for the president's meeting tomorrow with 
Ms. Albright, the special envoy of the U.S. President, namely 
that through the Foreign Ministry declaration issued yesterday, 
Bulgaria has expressed its approval of the Partnership for Peace 
initiative; that in the very near future our country will accept 
the invitation to sign a framework Partnership for Peace 
agreement; and that the Council of Ministers will form a working 
group to draft proposals for Bulgaria's specific participation 
in the partnership. (end recording) 

