<H3> <TI>   Croats, Muslims Agree Seek Cease-Fire Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301112594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1100 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301112594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Generals Ante Roso and Rasim Delic, commanders of 
the Croat and Muslim forces in Bosnia-Herzegovina, have agreed 
that they will determine a way to implement a cease-fire that is 
due to come into force on 15 January, the UN Protection Force in 
Sarajevo announced today. 
  The cease-fire should be proclaimed in accordance with an 
agreement concluded in Bonn between Croatian President Franjo 
Tudjman and Bosnian President Alija Izetbegovic. 
  Commanders Delic and Roso also agreed that they will begin 
negotiations on the exchange of POW's and the return of two 
Muslim army helicopters that have been held in Medjugorje for 
the past two months. 

