<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Fresh Defeat' of Abdic's Forces in Cazin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1201163394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1201163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Mirza Sadikovic report from the 5th Corps of the </F>
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army] 
  [Excerpt] The unsuccessful offensive by the members of the 
so-called [Velika] Kladusa autonomy and the Chetniks from the 
SAO [Serbian autonomous region of] Krajina on the free territory 
of Bihac, that is, parts of the Cazin commune, has continued 
today. Mindlessly attacking the area around Buzim, the 
separatists have suffered a fresh defeat. In a strong 
counterattack, members of the 5th Corps of the Army of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina captured two companies of separatists, about 
200 of them, together with a large amount of equipment, 
ammunition, and weapons. 
  Not only have they suffered a fresh defeat in this region, 
but Fikret [Abdic]'s separatists have simply being routed in the 
region of (?Trzac). A significant amount of ammunition and 
equipment was captured in the fighting there. They could not do 
anything else but resort to artillery. Thus, the areas of 
Pecigrad, Skokovi, and Vitkovac are coming under constant fire, 
where further material damage has been caused to residential 
property. Some civilians have also been wounded. 
  The reports from this region on the consolidation of the 
situation are encouraging. The population are slowly retuning 
to their homes. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

