<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council Issues Declarations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1201203494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
2000 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1201203494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Consultative Council for Romania's 
Euro-Atlantic Integration held a meeting today at the Senate 
headquarters in Bucharest. [passage omitted] 
  At the end of the meeting, the participants adopted a 
declaration on the results of the NATO summit meeting in 
Brussels. In this declaration, the Consultative Council for 
Romania's Euro-Atlantic Integration recommends that all 
political parties and institutions in Romania should openly 
support the effort of the country's integration in NATO, which 
is an essential goal of a policy devoted to guaranteeing our 
national security, as well as the European stability. 
  In another declaration, the members of the Consultative 
Council pledge to support, through relevant actions and means, 
the process of Romania's integration in the European Union. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

