<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iliescu Promulgates Government Ordinances Bill </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1201203194 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1201203194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today, Romania's President Ion Iliescu promulgated 
the bill empowering the government to rule by ordinances and 
authorizing it to contract and guarantee foreign loans, a 
communique received from Romania's Presidency says. 
  The promulgation was made on the basis of Decision No. 4 of 
11 January 1994 of the Constitutional Court, which found that 
parliament has observed the stipulations of the Constitution 
when it passed the aforementioned bill. 

</TEXT>

