<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Free Democrats Comment on `Partnership' Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301101594 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
0500 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Alliance of Free Democrats is dissatisfied with 
NATO's Partnership for Peace proposal, but having considered the 
realities, it acknowledges the proposal. This was said by 
Istvan Szent-Ivanyi, deputy chairman of parliament's foreign 
affairs committee, in Vienna. Regarding the Prague summit, the 
Free Democrat politician regrets that the Visegrad countries 
could not act in a united way. 

</TEXT>

