<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prisoner Exchange With Serbs Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201201394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1600 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201201394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An exchange of prisoners of war took place this 
afternoon at the UN Protection Force checkpoint near Lipovac. 
The Croatian side handed over 11 prisoners, mainly members of 
the Stit [Shield] terrorist group. One of the prisoners refused 
to go over to the Serbian side. In addition to eight people 
from the Sombor group, another five prisoners were released from 
Serbian prisons. Thus the agreement signed by Panic and Franjo 
Greguric in Budapest in 1992 has been realized. 

</TEXT>

