<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Vojvodina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fuel Shortage Threatens Spring Sowing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301103294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0553 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Novi Sad, 13 Jan (TANJUG) -- Vojvodina farmers 
failed to take advantage of the exceptionally favorable weather 
conditions, not recorded for a long time, to deep-plough almost 
1 million hectares of land in preparation for spring sowing. 
The main reason is the lack of fuel which the farmers expected 
to receive immediately after the autumn harvest. The province's 
Secretariat for Agriculture, the Vojvodina Chamber of Economy, 
and the Vojvodina Cooperative Union note that both the federal 
and the republic's government have, on several occasions, been 
asked to secure urgent diesel fuel deliveries but with to avail. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

