<H3> <TI>   Ministry Protests `False' Hungarian Information </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1401083494 Prague CTK in English 2349 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1401083494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, Jan 11 (CTK) -- Slovakia's Foreign 
Ministry said today it was concerned about the "unobjective 
information" on the meeting of Hungarian elected representatives 
in Komarno, south Slovakia, on January 8, spread by the 
Hungarian Government Office for Hungarian Ethnic Minorities 
Abroad. The ministry handed the protest to the charge 
d'affaires of the Hungarian Embassy in Slovakia, Ferenc Boros. 
  The protest says that the information, destined for foreign 
diplomatic missions, is provided "out of context" and is 
"unobjective and misleading." Providing false information on 
developments in Slovakia by Hungarian authorities does not serve 
good neighborly relations, the protest says. 
  It warns that misleading information on the ongoing process 
of the territorial administrative arrangement of Slovakia could 
assume the character of interference in Slovakia's internal 
affairs. 

</TEXT>

