<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Levels of Trust in Institutions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1401102094 Prague CTK in English 1328 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1401102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, Jan 13 (CTK) -- The most trusted 
institution in Slovakia is the Slovak Army, according to an 
opinion poll conducted by the Slovak Statistical Bureau. 
  After omitting answers such as "I don't know," the following 
institutions were deemed most trusted by Slovaks: Army, 
president, Church, unions, Police, Parliament, courts, and 
prosecutor, and, lastly, the government. 
  The research showed a higher level of mistrust than trust in 
state bodies. Only two out of eight institutions earned more 
trust than mistrust: the Army and the president. 

</TEXT>

