<H3> <TI>   Serbs Taxing Albanian Salaries for War </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1301155394 Tirana ATA in English 1122 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1301155394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 13 (ATA) -- In yesterday's press 
conference, the chairman of the Union of the Independent Trade 
Unions of Kosova, Dr. Hajrullah Gorani, informed reporters that 
Serbia has to compensate with 3 billion U.S. dollars the 
Albanian workers who were violently dismissed from their jobs. 
  Reporters were also informed of a document from the 
heat-power stations of Kosova, which are under Serbian violent 
measures, according to which the finance sector is ordered to 
take 2 per cent of the income of each worker for the war. 

</TEXT>

