<H3> <TI>   Minister Says 6,700 Croats Released by Serbs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301162894 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in English 1303 
GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301162894 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At today's session of the Croatian Government, its 
minister in charge of humanitarian affairs, Ivica Kostovic, 
spoke about the efforts Croatia has undertaken for the release 
of POW's from Serbia's detention camps. So far 6,700 Croats 
have been released, Kostovic said, and we trust the others will 
also be freed. He added that normal constructive negotiations 
on this issue conducted with the representatives of the 
so-called Federal Republic of Yugoslavia had opened other 
possibilities of successful negotiations in the future. 

