<H3> <TI>   Japanese Delegation Assessing Investment Plans </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301144694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1132 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Skopje, 13 Jan (Tanjug) -- A delegation of the 
Japanese Ministry of Foreign Affairs, led by Shunji Yanai, 
director general of the Foreign Policy Bureau, is visiting 
Skopje today. According to a statement by the UN Protection 
Forces [UNPROFOR] Command for Macedonia, the Japanese delegation 
will meet with representatives of the Macedonian Government and 
will also visit UNPROFOR members at an observation point near 
Tabanovci. The Japanese delegation is visiting Macedonia as 
part of its fact-finding tour of the former Yugoslav republics, 
on the basis of which it will decide on possible financial 
investments. 

</TEXT>

