<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Food Imports Adding to Slovakia Trade Deficit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301145094 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1100 
GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301145094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Food imports from the Czech Republic have added at 
least 1 billion korunas to Slovakia's deficit in the balance of 
payments with the Czech Republic. 
  According to Milan Filo, director of the Department of Trade 
at the Slovak Ministry of Agriculture, such imports are the 
result of the surviving federal structure of agriculture, which 
concentrates final food production in the Czech Republic. Among 
the main produce still imported by Slovakia are poultry, dairy 
and bakery products, margarine, spirits, and tobacco. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

